HEADWORD: Rollichie
<hw>Rol"li*chie</hw>.]</mhw>
<ety>[D. <ets>rolletje</ets> a little roll.]</ety> <def>A kind of
sausage, made in a bag of tripe, sliced and fried, famous among the
Dutch of New Amsterdam and still known, esp. in New Jersey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

